1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,570
Hi, this is PolicyPay Agent:

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:04,690
a policy-bound autonomous payment agent built on
Sui.

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:07,650
It targets the Agentic Web track because the

4
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:09,730
agent can observe state, plan an action,

5
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:12,930
transact on Sui, and coordinate recurring
payments.

6
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:14,690
But it can only do that inside boundaries

7
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:16,210
enforced by Move.

8
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:19,333
Recurring crypto payments are still awkward for
teams,

9
00:00:19,363 --> 00:00:21,093
DAOs, and small protocol treasuries.

10
00:00:21,123 --> 00:00:24,213
Manual multisig workflows are safe,

11
00:00:24,243 --> 00:00:24,853
but slow.

12
00:00:24,883 --> 00:00:27,973
Generic automation is fast, but it can become

13
00:00:28,003 --> 00:00:28,453
too powerful.

14
00:00:28,483 --> 00:00:31,573
PolicyPay separates automation from authority.

15
00:00:31,603 --> 00:00:34,294
The owner connects a Sui wallet and creates

16
00:00:34,324 --> 00:00:34,774
an AgentVault.

17
00:00:34,804 --> 00:00:38,054
Before signing, the owner defines the agent's
hard

18
00:00:38,084 --> 00:00:40,454
limits: maximum spend per payment,

19
00:00:40,484 --> 00:00:43,414
rolling-window spend limit, minimum reserve
balance,

20
00:00:43,444 --> 00:00:46,774
expiration time, and the agent wallet that will

21
00:00:46,804 --> 00:00:47,494
receive the scoped session capability.

22
00:00:47,524 --> 00:00:50,016
This is not just UI state.

23
00:00:50,046 --> 00:00:52,896
These boundaries are encoded into the Move
object

24
00:00:52,926 --> 00:00:53,296
model.

25
00:00:53,326 --> 00:00:55,296
When the vault is created,

26
00:00:55,326 --> 00:00:57,296
Sui produces three important objects.

27
00:00:57,326 --> 00:01:00,656
The shared AgentVault holds funds and policy.

28
00:01:00,686 --> 00:01:03,376
The owner keeps the OwnerCap for administration.

29
00:01:03,406 --> 00:01:05,808
The agent receives only an AgentSessionCap,

30
00:01:05,838 --> 00:01:09,328
which can execute approved payment rules but
cannot

31
00:01:09,358 --> 00:01:11,808
withdraw arbitrary funds or add new recipients.

32
00:01:11,838 --> 00:01:15,488
Next, the owner deposits SUI into the vault

33
00:01:15,518 --> 00:01:18,643
and adds a recurring payment rule.

34
00:01:18,673 --> 00:01:21,203
The rule stores the recipient,

35
00:01:21,233 --> 00:01:23,603
amount, schedule, nonce, and active state
onchain.

36
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:26,643
That means prompt injection or backend bugs
cannot

37
00:01:26,673 --> 00:01:29,256
silently change who gets paid or how much

38
00:01:29,286 --> 00:01:29,656
gets paid.

39
00:01:29,686 --> 00:01:31,976
The agent service observes the vault,

40
00:01:32,006 --> 00:01:34,696
finds due rules, previews the plan,

41
00:01:34,726 --> 00:01:36,296
risk-checks it, and submits the payment
transaction

42
00:01:36,326 --> 00:01:37,576
with the agent key.

43
00:01:37,606 --> 00:01:39,816
The backend helps automate execution,

44
00:01:39,846 --> 00:01:41,656
but it is not the source of authority.

45
00:01:41,686 --> 00:01:43,096
The Move contract is.

46
00:01:43,126 --> 00:01:45,712
The most important part is the failure path.

47
00:01:45,742 --> 00:01:48,272
If the agent tries to pay too early,

48
00:01:48,302 --> 00:01:51,552
exceed the per-payment limit, cross the
rolling-window

49
00:01:51,582 --> 00:01:53,312
limit, drain below the reserve,

50
00:01:53,342 --> 00:01:55,792
or continue after pause or revoke,

51
00:01:55,822 --> 00:01:58,485
the Move call aborts and funds do not

52
00:01:58,515 --> 00:01:58,805
move.

53
00:01:58,835 --> 00:02:01,765
Every meaningful step leaves Sui evidence:

54
00:02:01,795 --> 00:02:05,285
package id, vault objects, transaction digest,

55
00:02:05,315 --> 00:02:07,205
object state, and events.

56
00:02:07,235 --> 00:02:09,525
In the recording, I open Sui Explorer and

57
00:02:09,555 --> 00:02:13,244
verify the package and transaction directly on
Testnet.

58
00:02:13,274 --> 00:02:15,804
PolicyPay turns Sui object ownership and
capabilities

59
00:02:15,834 --> 00:02:18,524
into payment rails for autonomous agents:

60
00:02:18,554 --> 00:02:21,244
the agent can act, but only inside verifiable

61
00:02:21,274 --> 00:02:22,912
user-defined boundaries.
